{
  "texts": [
    "This result suggests that predicting the principal diagnosis or procedure without considering CC/MCC is a significantly easier task on its own.",
    "Upon integrating a mapping rule designed to infer DRGs through the combination of base DRG and CC/MCC labels, the accuracy reached 51.5% across all DRGs.",
    "Notably, this performance was comparable with the accuracy attained in the single-label approach of 52.0% using the same base model, showing that the LLM was able to achieve state-of-the-art performance via either classification setting.",
    "As noted above, a correlation exists between the number of training cases and prediction performance.",
    "DRGs with a top-5 prediction accuracy exceeding 80% are associated with a median of 309 training cases per label."
  ]
}